#timestamp 4:12:00

Using FastAPI 0.116.1 and python version = 3.13.1
Postman for testing the API w/o needing more frontend development
Use uvicorn main:app to start the server , add --reload to auto reload on code changes

1. Create venv: python -m venv myenv
2. Activate it and install FastAPI using pip or from requirements file
pip install "fastapi[standard]"
or
pip install -r requirements.txt

DOCUMENTATION
Available by going to http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs

DATABASE
using postgres: Freely-Erased7-Headsman
pgadmin4 GUI
Using Psycopg 3 to link python to postgres
    Make sure to properly add libpq to your PATH environment variable
    https://www.psycopg.org/psycopg3/docs/basic/installation


FLOW
We are following a pydantic model to define how the data should be structured
This model is followed when using psycopg to interact with the database